concepts.OV,_ECOG_PERFORMANCE_STATUS_114_DESC: 0: Fully active, able to carry on all pre-disease performance without restriction 1: Restricted in physically strenuous activity but ambulatory and able to carry out work of a light or sedentary nature, 2: Ambulatory and capable of all self-care but unable to carry out any work activities. Up and about more than 50% of waking hours 3: Capable of only limited self-care, confined to bed or chair more than 50% of waking hours 4: Completely disabled. Cannot carry out any selfcare; totally confined to bed or chair 5: Dead
